workflow.name: Automated developer onboarding audit with ClickUp, GPT-4o-mini, and Slack alerts
workflow.description:
## Description:
Automate your developer onboarding quality checks with this n8n workflow template.
 Whenever a new onboarding task is created in ClickUp, the workflow logs it to Google Sheets, evaluates its completeness using Azure OpenAI GPT-4o-mini, and alerts your team in Slack if critical details are missing.
Perfect for engineering managers, DevOps leads, and HR tech teams who want to maintain consistent onboarding quality and ensure every developer gets the tools, credentials, and environment setup they need ‚Äî without manual review.

## ‚úÖ What This Template Does (Step-by-Step)

‚ö° Step 1: Auto-Trigger on ClickUp Task Creation
 Listens for new task creation events (taskCreated) in your ClickUp workspace to initiate the audit automatically.

üìä Step 2: Log Task Details to Google Sheets
 Records essential task data ‚Äî task name, assignee, and description ‚Äî creating a central audit trail for all onboarding activities.

üß† Step 3: AI Completeness Analysis (GPT-4o-mini)
Uses Azure OpenAI GPT-4o-mini to evaluate each onboarding task for completeness across key areas:
- Tooling requirements
- Credential setup
- Environment configuration
- Instruction clarity
Outputs:
‚úÖ Score (0‚Äì100)
‚ö†Ô∏è List of Missing Items
üí° Suggestions for Improvement
üö¶ Step 4: Apply Quality Gate
 Checks whether the AI-generated completeness 

score is below 80. Incomplete tasks automatically move to the alert stage for review.

üì¢ Step 5: Alert Team via Slack
 Sends a structured Slack message summarizing the issue, including:
1. Task name & assignee
2. Completeness score
3. Missing checklist items
4. Recommended next actions
This ensures your team fixes incomplete onboarding items before they impact new hires.

## üß† Key Features
 ü§ñ AI-driven task completeness scoring
 üìä Automatic task logging for audit visibility
 ‚öôÔ∏è Smart quality gate (score threshold < 80)
 üì¢ Instant Slack alerts for incomplete tasks
 üîÑ End-to-end automation from ClickUp to Slack

## üíº Use Cases
 üéì Audit onboarding checklists for new developers
 üß© Standardize environment setup and credential handover
 üö® Identify missing steps before onboarding deadlines
 üìà Maintain onboarding consistency across teams

## üì¶ Required Integrations
1. ClickUp API ‚Äì to detect new onboarding tasks
2. Google Sheets API ‚Äì to store audit logs and history
3. Azure OpenAI (GPT-4o-mini) ‚Äì to evaluate completeness
4. Slack API ‚Äì to alert the team on incomplete entries

## üéØ Why Use This Template?
 ‚úÖ Ensures every new developer receives a full, ready-to-start setup
 ‚úÖ Eliminates manual checklist verification
 ‚úÖ Improves onboarding quality and compliance tracking
 ‚úÖ Creates a transparent audit trail for continuous improvement

parameters.content:
## 1. Capture New Tasks

Triggers whenever a task is created in your ClickUp workspace.

## 2. Data Preparation

Extracts and formats task details for logging and AI analysis.

## 3. AI Quality Analysis

GPT-4o-mini evaluates task completeness and scores it 0-100.

parameters.text:
=Analyze this developer onboarding task for completeness:

Task: {{ $json.task }}
Description: {{ $json.description }}

Evaluate these critical areas:
1. **Tooling** (25 pts): Are required tools, IDEs, packages mentioned?
2. **Credentials** (25 pts): Are account setups, API keys, access instructions covered?
3. **Environment** (25 pts): Are local configs, dependencies, setup steps explained?
4. **Documentation** (25 pts): Are instructions clear with examples?

Provide your response in this exact format:
Score: [number 0-100]
Missing: [comma-separated list]
Recommendations: [specific improvements]
Status: [Complete/Incomplete]

parameters.content:
## 4. Parse & Route

Extracts AI score and routes to appropriate path based on quality threshold.

## 5. Alert & Remediation

Incomplete tasks trigger Slack notifications with improvement suggestions.

## 6. Success Path

Complete tasks get verified status and positive feedback.

parameters.commentText:
=‚úÖ **Quality Audit Passed**

This task scored {{ $json.score }}/100 and meets our onboarding standards. Great work!

parameters.content:
## 7. Analytics Tracking

Logs all results for performance tracking and trend analysis.

## How it works

This workflow automatically audits developer onboarding tasks created in ClickUp. When a new task is created, AI analyzes it for completeness across tooling, credentials, and environment setup. Tasks scoring below 60% trigger Slack alerts and get flagged for improvement. Complete tasks are marked as verified.

## Setup steps

1. **Connect ClickUp**: Add your workspace team ID
2. **Link Google Sheets**: Create a sheet with columns: Task name, Assignee, Description, Status
3. **Configure Azure OpenAI**: Add your API credentials for GPT-4o-mini
4. **Set Slack channel**: Choose where to send quality alerts
5. **Adjust threshold**: Modify the 60% score threshold in the filter node if needed

The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
